<TITLE> World must trust Bangladesh's anti-terror stance: ministry </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 07 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh is firm to resist any form of terrorism, the foreign ministry said in a statement Friday, a day after the US termed Harakat ul-Jihad Al Islami, Bangladesh (HUJI-B) a global terrorist outfit. The ministry also said Bangladesh banned the Islamist outfit several years ago. "The international community is expected to believe that Bangladesh is firmly committed to resisting any form of terrorism," the foreign ministry said. US Secretary of State Condoleeza Rice Thursday under an executive order branded HUJI as an international terrorist organisation. bdn
